AB  - Ad hoc network is a temporary multi-hop wireless computer communication network that is composed of mobile hosts communicating with each other through wireless links. Dynamic topology is a typical character. A new QoS routing algorithm for mobile Ad Hoc networks, which is named QoS-aware self-adaptive routing algorithm(QA-SARA), is proposed in this paper. It integrates the multiple QoS parameters of traffic into one request that is represented by integrated judgment. QA-SARA compares the integrated QoS value of each path and selects the most appropriate one according to the operation rules. Simulation results show that QA-SARA can tolerate the imprecise information which is caused by the dynamic network topology well while supporting QoS function.
